From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000003 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: SmoothNAS ops <ops@smoothnas.invalid>
Date: Thu, 24 Apr 2026 16:00:00 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] sunrpc: bump RPC_DEF_SLOT_TABLE from 16 to 128

On a 2.5 Gbps LAN NFSv4.2 backup against a real source we measured
sustained throughput going from 2.05 Gbps (82% of line) to 2.30 Gbps
(92% of line) just by writing 128 to
/sys/module/sunrpc/parameters/tcp_slot_table_entries before mount.
The workload was 14.23 GB / 909 files (avg ~15 MB, long tail of
sub-MB media). With the upstream default of 16 slots, the
per-file LOOKUP/OPEN/READ/CLOSE RPCs that dominate small-file
throughput on a single TCP connection serialise at depth 16 and
leave the pipe underutilised.

The auto-grow path in xprt_alloc_slot still expands up to
RPC_MAX_SLOT_TABLE_LIMIT (65536) at runtime, but only after it
observes congestion on the existing slot table. Seeding the
initial window higher avoids the first few seconds of a fresh
mount being bottlenecked on a window that's about to grow anyway.

Userspace can still override the initial value via
  sysctl sunrpc.tcp_slot_table_entries=<N>
or at boot via
  sunrpc.tcp_slot_table_entries=<N>
and smoothnas tierd sets 128 explicitly on every boot. This patch
bakes the same value into the appliance-shipped kernel so mounts
that happen before tierd's tuning phase (initramfs rescue paths,
systemd early mnt-* units ordered ahead of tierd.service) pick up
the same setting.

No ABI change. RPC_MIN_SLOT_TABLE stays at 2 and
RPC_MAX_SLOT_TABLE_LIMIT stays at 65536.

Signed-off-by: SmoothNAS ops <ops@smoothnas.invalid>
---
 include/linux/sunrpc/xprt.h | 2 +-
 1 file changed, 1 insertion(+), 1 deletion(-)

diff --git a/include/linux/sunrpc/xprt.h b/include/linux/sunrpc/xprt.h
--- a/include/linux/sunrpc/xprt.h
+++ b/include/linux/sunrpc/xprt.h
@@ -20,7 +20,7 @@
 #include <linux/sunrpc/msg_prot.h>

 #define RPC_MIN_SLOT_TABLE	(2U)
-#define RPC_DEF_SLOT_TABLE	(16U)
+#define RPC_DEF_SLOT_TABLE	(128U)
 #define RPC_MAX_SLOT_TABLE_LIMIT	(65536U)
 #define RPC_MAX_SLOT_TABLE	RPC_MAX_SLOT_TABLE_LIMIT

--
2.40.0
